# xv6-RISC-V Enhanced

An enhanced version of the xv6-RISC-V teaching operating system,
originally developed by MIT. This version extends the base xv6 with
several new features including an improved interactive shell, file
management commands, orphan process demonstrations, and new kernel-level
system calls.

---

## Enhancements Over Base xv6

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Enhanced Shell** | Command history, up/down arrow navigation, tab completion |
| **`cp` command** | Copy files with proper directory-aware destination handling |
| **`mv` command** | Move/rename files using fast link+unlink strategy |
| **`forphan`** | Demonstrates controlled orphan process reclamation |
| **`dorphan`** | Demonstrates detached daemon-style orphan process |
| **`getppid` syscall** | New kernel syscall returning parent process ID |
| **`ps` syscall** | New kernel syscall listing all active processes |

---

## Building and Running

### Prerequisites

You will need:
- A RISC-V GCC cross-compiler toolchain
- QEMU compiled for riscv64 (minimum version 7.2)

---

### Windows (WSL2) — Recommended for Windows Users

**Step 1: Install WSL2 with Ubuntu**
```powershell
# Run in PowerShell as Administrator
wsl --install
# Restart your PC after installation
```

**Step 2: Open Ubuntu terminal and install dependencies**
```bash
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y
sudo apt-get install -y git build-essential qemu-system-misc \
    gcc-riscv64-linux-gnu binutils-riscv64-linux-gnu
```

**Step 3: Clone and run**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Silawalaryan/xv6-riscV-enhanced.git
cd xv6-riscv-enhanced
make qemu
```

---

### Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)

**Step 1: Install dependencies**
```bash
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y
sudo apt-get install -y git build-essential qemu-system-misc \
    gcc-riscv64-linux-gnu binutils-riscv64-linux-gnu
```

**Step 2: Clone and run**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Silawalaryan/xv6-riscV-enhanced.git
cd xv6-riscv-enhanced
make qemu
```

---

### macOS

**Step 1: Install Homebrew if not already installed**
```bash
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
```

**Step 2: Install dependencies**
```bash
brew tap riscv-software-src/riscv
brew install riscv-tools
brew install qemu
```

**Step 3: Clone and run**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Silawalaryan/xv6-riscV-enhanced.git
cd xv6-riscv-enhanced
make qemu
```

---

## Running the OS

Once xv6 boots you will see:
```
xv6 kernel is booting
hart 1 starting
hart 2 starting
init: starting sh
$
```

The `$` is the xv6 shell. Try the following commands:
```sh
# List all available programs
ls

# Test the ps system call
ps

# Test the getppid system call
getppid

# Test file copy
cp README README2
ls

# Test file move
mv README2 README3
ls

# Test shell history
echo hello
ls
history


**To exit QEMU:** Press `Ctrl + A` then `X`

---

## Project Structure
```
xv6-riscv-enhanced/
├── kernel/
│   ├── console.c     ← Modified: arrow key and char-at-a-time support
│   ├── syscall.c     ← Modified: registered getppid and ps syscalls
│   ├── syscall.h     ← Modified: added SYS_getppid and SYS_ps
│   └── sysproc.c     ← Modified: implemented sys_getppid and sys_ps
├── user/
│   ├── sh.c          ← Modified: history, arrow keys, tab completion
│   ├── cp.c          ← New: file copy command
│   ├── mv.c          ← New: file move/rename command
│   ├── ps.c          ← New: process list user program
│   ├── getppid.c     ← New: getppid test user program
│   ├── forphan.c     ← New: orphan process reclamation demo
│   └── dorphan.c     ← New: detached orphan process demo
├── mkfs/
│   └── mkfs.c        ← Filesystem image builder
└── Makefile          ← Modified: added new user programs
```

